      <p style="margin:0.4rem 0 0; font-size:0.9rem;">Three 木 (trees) together make a forest. No story needed — the meaning is literally shown by repeating the radical three times.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#f0fdf4; border:1px solid #bbf7d0; border-radius:0.5rem; padding:1rem;">
      <div style="font-size:2.5rem; text-align:center; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">休</div>
      <strong>Rest (yasumu)</strong>
      <p style="margin:0.4rem 0 0; font-size:0.9rem;">A person (亻) leaning against a tree (木) for a rest in the shade. The two components tell the whole story.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#f0fdf4; border:1px solid #bbf7d0; border-radius:0.5rem; padding:1rem;">
      <div style="font-size:2.5rem; text-align:center; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">明</div>
      <strong>Bright (akarui)</strong>
      <p style="margin:0.4rem 0 0; font-size:0.9rem;">Sun (日) plus moon (月) together — when both the sun and moon shine, everything is bright. A beautifully logical compound.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#f0fdf4; border:1px solid #bbf7d0; border-radius:0.5rem; padding:1rem;">
